name: Vincent Lee, et al., Appellants, v. Ruth M. Maguire, Appellee

judges: Whitfield, P. J., and Strum and Buford, J. J., concur.
parties: Vincent Lee, et al., Appellants, v. Ruth M. Maguire, Appellee.

opinions.text:
Per Curiam.
This cause having heretofore been submitted to the Court upon the transcripe of the record of the Decree herein, and briefs and argument of counsl for the respective farties, and the record having been seen and inspected, and the Court being now advised of its judgment to be given in'the premises, it seems to the Court that there is no error in the said Decree; it is, therefore, considered, ordered and adjudged by the Court that the said Decree of the Circuit Court be, and the same is hereby affirmed.
Whitfield, P. J., and Strum and Buford, J. J., concur.
opinions.author: Per Curiam.
